This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it discusses the development of a semantic parser that maps natural language questions to logical forms. Additionally, the paper proposes a new semantic formalism, dependency-based compositional semantics (DCS), which is a common topic in the field of natural language processing. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, such as log-linear distribution and numerical optimization, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on semantic parsing and information retrieval also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
